wikipedia_page.main: James Hannen, Baron Hannen, PC, FRS (19 March 1821 – 29 March 1894) was an English judge and vegetarian.

response: He was the second son of Sir Charles Hall (1814–1883) and his wife, Sarah née Duval. After attending Harrow School, he studied at Trinity College, Cambridge, and under James Hannen, Baron Hannen at Lincoln's Inn.
